org.cougaar.core.qos.metrics
Interface MetricsService

All Superinterfaces:
Service
All Known Implementing Classes:
NullMetricsServiceImpl, RSSMetricsServiceImpl
public interface MetricsService
extends Service

This is the query interface to the metrics services. The two basic operations, query and unubscribe, have several optional paramters, which is wny each comes in four variants. The structure of paths is defined in the Metrics Services html documenation and won't be covered here.

getValue

Metric getValue(java.lang.String path,
                VariableEvaluator evaluator,
                java.util.Properties qos_tags)
Retrieves the current value at the given path. The path can include special context-dependent variables whose runtime value will be determined by the evaluator. For now the qos_tags are not used.

getValue

Metric getValue(java.lang.String path,
                java.util.Properties qos_tags)
Retrieves the current value at the given path. No context-dependent variable handling will be done. For now the qos_tags are not used.

getValue

Metric getValue(java.lang.String path)
Retrieves the current value at the given path. No context-dependent variable handling will be done.

subscribeToValue

java.lang.Object subscribeToValue(java.lang.String path,
                                  java.util.Observer observer,
                                  VariableEvaluator evaluator,
                                  MetricNotificationQualifier qualifier)
Subscribes the given observer to the given path. The usual Observer api will be used for callbacks. The path can include special context-dependent variables whose runtime value will be determined by the evaluator. Ordinarily a callback will be invoked whenever the value at the path changes. This can be restricted with the qualifier.

subscribeToValue

java.lang.Object subscribeToValue(java.lang.String path,
                                  java.util.Observer observer,
                                  VariableEvaluator evaluator)
Subscribes the given observer to the given path. The usual Observer api will be used for callbacks. The path can include special context-dependent variables whose runtime value will be determined by the evaluator. No restrictions are imposed on the callbacks, which will be invoked whenever the value at the path changes.

subscribeToValue

java.lang.Object subscribeToValue(java.lang.String path,
                                  java.util.Observer observer,
                                  MetricNotificationQualifier qualifier)
Subscribes the given observer to the given path. The usual Observer api will be used for callbacks. No context-dependent variable handling will be done. Ordinarily a callback will be invoked whenever the value at the path changes. This can be restricted with the qualifier.

subscribeToValue

java.lang.Object subscribeToValue(java.lang.String path,
                                  java.util.Observer observer)
Subscribes the given observer to the given path. The usual Observer api will be used for callbacks. No context-dependent variable handling will be done, and no restrictions are imposed on the callbacks, which will be invoked whenever the value at the path changes.

unsubscribeToValue

void unsubscribeToValue(java.lang.Object subscription_handle)
End a previously established subscription. The handle is as returned by one of the subscribeToValue calls.
